# titarchconfig

Personal Arch Linux config, managed with chezmoi.

## Layout
- `home/` - chezmoi source state (`.chezmoiroot` points here). Filenames use
  chezmoi's encoding: `dot_` = leading dot, `executable_` = exec bit,
  `.tmpl` = Go template (per-machine values from `~/.config/chezmoi/chezmoi.toml`).
- `system/` - root-owned files (X11/sunshine/udev); deploy with
  `sudo system/install-system.sh`.
- `gpg/` - public key material.
- `install.sh` - interactive bootstrap for a new machine (packages, oh-my-zsh,
  chezmoi deploy).
- `_legacy/` - untracked graveyard for retired configs.

## Daily use
- Edit files here (or `chezmoi edit <target>`), then `chezmoi apply`.
- `chezmoi diff` - what would change on this machine.
- `chezmoi status` / `chezmoi managed` - sync state.
- After editing a live file directly under `$HOME`: `chezmoi re-add <target>`.

## New machine
    sudo pacman -S chezmoi git
    chezmoi init --apply <repo-url>     # prompts for per-machine data
or run `./install.sh` for the full guided setup.

On this machine (grodarch) the source dir is pinned to `~/titarchconfig`
via `sourceDir` in `~/.config/chezmoi/chezmoi.toml`.
